    • Method Detail

      • getTrackingLegs

        public ListResponse<LegResponse> getTrackingLegs(Long accountId,
                                        Long ownerId,
                                        Long startDate,
                                        Long endDate,
                                        String tags,
                                        Boolean getLastPoint)
                                          throws SirqulException
        Retrieve tracking data to be able to show where a user has been.

        Target API Endpoint: /tracking/search
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required)
        ownerId - the account id of the person the user wants to tracking data for
        startDate - the start date in (UTC milliseconds) to filter the tracking results. If no startDate is passed in, the last 30 days will be returned.
        endDate - the end date in (UTC milliseconds) to filter the tracking results
        tags - filter results by tag
        getLastPoint - gets the last known location of the user
        Returns:
        ListResponse<LegResponse> on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • saveTrackingLeg

        public SirqulResponse saveTrackingLeg(Long accountId,
                             Double distance,
                             Long duration,
                             Location startLocation,
                             Long startDate,
                             Location endLocation,
                             Long endDate,
                             List<TrackingStep> steps)
                               throws SirqulException
        Send tracking points to be able to generate pathing data.

        Target API Endpoint: /tracking
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required)
        distance - the total distance
        duration - the total duration
        startLocation - the location of the first point
        startDate - the start date (in UTC milliseconds) of the first point
        endLocation - the location of the last point
        endDate - the end date (in UTC milliseconds) of the last point
        steps - JSON array of tracking vectors used for smoother pathing data. Format is: 
         
 [
     {
         "endLat": 47.785834,
         "endLng": -122.406417,
         "distance": 0,
         "endDate": 1361840740845,
         "startLat": 47.785834,
         "startLng": -122.406417,
         "startDate": 1361840740845,
         "duration": 0
     },
     {
         "endLat": 47.785834,
         "endLng": -122.406417,
         "distance": 0,
         "endDate": 1361840745844,
         "startLat": 47.785834,
         "startLng": -122.406417,
         "startDate": 1361840740845,
         "duration": 4999
     }
 ]
        Returns:
        a SirqulResponse with a message of success or failure.
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.
